 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-djt","title":"Add request ID generation and tracking","description":"# Task: Add Request ID Generation and Tracking

## Parent Epic
[Epic] Request ID Enhancement (flywheel_gateway-483)

## Objective
Generate unique request IDs for every request and include them in responses and logs.

## Current State
- correlationId exists but may be shared across requests
- No dedicated request ID in responses
- No Request-Id header

## Deliverables

### 1. Request ID Generator
```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/middleware/request-id.ts

import { ulid } from "ulid";  // Or nanoid

/**
 * Generate a unique request ID.
 * Format: req_01H1234567890ABCDEFGHIJK
 */
export function generateRequestId(): string {
  return `req_${ulid().toLowerCase()}`;
}
```

### 2. Middleware to Attach Request ID
```typescript
import { Context, Next } from "hono";

export function requestIdMiddleware() {
  return async (c: Context, next: Next) => {
    // Check if client provided a request ID (for tracing)
    const clientRequestId = c.req.header("X-Request-Id");

    // Generate server request ID
    const requestId = generateRequestId();

    // Store in context
    c.set("requestId", requestId);
    c.set("clientRequestId", clientRequestId);

    // Process request
    await next();

    // Add to response headers
    c.header("X-Request-Id", requestId);
    if (clientRequestId) {
      c.header("X-Client-Request-Id", clientRequestId);
    }
  };
}
```

### 3. Integrate with Logging
```typescript
// Update logger context
const log = getLogger();

// In request handler
log.info({ requestId: c.get("requestId") }, "Processing request");

// Or via middleware
export function loggingMiddleware() {
  return async (c: Context, next: Next) => {
    const requestId = c.get("requestId");
    const startTime = Date.now();

    // Add to all logs in this request
    const log = logger.child({ requestId });
    c.set("log", log);

    log.info({ method: c.req.method, path: c.req.path }, "Request started");

    await next();

    log.info(
      { status: c.res.status, durationMs: Date.now() - startTime },
      "Request completed"
    );
  };
}
```

### 4. Include in Response Envelope
Update response utilities to include requestId:
```typescript
export function wrapResource<T>(
  objectType: string,
  data: T,
  options: WrapOptions = {}
): ApiResponse<T> {
  return {
    object: objectType,
    data,
    requestId: options.requestId ?? "unknown",  // Should come from context
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    ...(options.links && { links: options.links }),
  };
}
```

### 5. Hono Integration
```typescript
// In route handlers
return sendResource(c, "agent", data, 200);
// sendResource automatically gets requestId from context

// Implementation
export function sendResource<T>(...) {
  const requestId = c.get("requestId");
  return c.json(wrapResource(objectType, data, { requestId, links }), status);
}
```

## ID Format
Using ULID with `req_` prefix:
- `req_01h1z3abc4def5ghi6jkl7mno`
- Sortable by time (useful for log analysis)
- URL-safe
- 26 characters (compact)

Alternative: Nanoid
- `req_V1StGXR8_Z5jdHi6B-myT`
- Shorter but not sortable

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Request ID generated for every request
- [ ] ID in context, available to all handlers
- [ ] ID in X-Request-Id response header
- [ ] ID in response body (requestId field)
- [ ] ID included in all log entries
- [ ] Client X-Request-Id echoed as X-Client-Request-Id
- [ ] Tests verify ID presence

## Testing
```typescript
describe("request ID", () => {
  it("generates unique ID per request", async () => {
    const res1 = await app.request("/health");
    const res2 = await app.request("/health");

    const id1 = res1.headers.get("X-Request-Id");
    const id2 = res2.headers.get("X-Request-Id");

    expect(id1).toMatch(/^req_/);
    expect(id1).not.toBe(id2);
  });

  it("includes ID in response body", async () => {
    const res = await app.request("/agents");
    const body = await res.json();

    expect(body.requestId).toMatch(/^req_/);
  });

  it("echoes client request ID", async () => {
    const res = await app.request("/health", {
      headers: { "X-Request-Id": "client-123" },
    });

    expect(res.headers.get("X-Client-Request-Id")).toBe("client-123");
  });
});
```

## Dependencies
- Depends on: Response Structure Standardization (to include in envelope)

